post_text:
District Spirit Week! Shelter in Place (SIP) Style!
Week of April 13, 2020

Make it Monday!
Draw a picture of your school mascot and wear your school colors. Extra points when you combine the Otter and Knight! Send a pic to your teacher!

Tell Someone Tuesday!
Make some “Kind Notes” and hide them around the house for someone to find, your new teacher might need some appreciation.

Work out Wednesday!
Spell your name and do a workout – see attached photo

Thirsty Thursday!
Create the ultimate milkshake, yum!

Friday Night Family SIP Date Night
Plan a Shelter in Place date night for your family, dinner, popcorn and Netflix, dessert…

-Take pictures and send them to your teacher – you may end up on Facebook!

post_text:
A question came up about other collaboration app available for distance learning. We wanted to share the response for our entire community.
The district is asking our teachers to utilize Google Classroom as our distance learning platform for students. We know that Google Classroom and Classroom Dojo are compliant with student privacy policies as mandated by the US Department of Education. Free platforms are typically not compliant, which can put students' privacy at risk.
